1
00:00:01,376 --> 00:00:04,087
DOCTOR: The Fourth Great
and Bountiful Human Empire.

2
00:00:04,171 --> 00:00:07,132
Every single fact in the Empire
beams out of this place.

3
00:00:07,257 --> 00:00:08,800
Now, that's what I call power.

4
00:00:08,884 --> 00:00:12,513
Six hundred channels, all coming out of
Satellite Five, broadcasting everywhere.

5
00:00:12,596 --> 00:00:14,640
This technology's wrong.

6
00:00:16,058 --> 00:00:17,559
-Trouble?
-Oh, yeah.

7
00:00:17,643 --> 00:00:20,687
This is not the Fourth Great
and Bountiful Human Empire.

8
00:00:20,771 --> 00:00:25,025
It's a place where humans are allowed to live
by kind permission of my client.

9
00:00:25,234 --> 00:00:26,485
Who controls Satellite Five?

10
00:00:27,152 --> 00:00:30,906
THE EDITOR: The Mighty Jagrafess
of the Holy Hadrojassic Maxarodenfoe.

11
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,825
You mean that thing's
in charge of Satellite Five?

12
00:00:33,909 --> 00:00:36,787
Once you go to Floor 500,
you never come back.

13
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:49,007
You'll have to stay and explain it,
no one's going to believe me.

14
00:00:49,091 --> 00:00:50,884
They might start believing
a lot of things now.

15
00:00:50,968 --> 00:00:53,679
The human race should accelerate,
all back to normal.

16
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:06,233
What's happening?

17
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,322
WOMAN: Oh, my God!

18
00:01:13,532 --> 00:01:16,535
I don't believe it!
Why did they put you in there?

19
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:18,579
They never said you were coming.

20
00:01:18,662 --> 00:01:20,289
What happened? I was...

21
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:24,459
Careful now.
Ooh, mind yourself.

22
00:01:24,543 --> 00:01:26,670
That's the transmat,
it scrambles your head.

23
00:01:26,795 --> 00:01:29,965
I was sick for days.
All right?

24
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:34,761
So, what's your name,
then, sweetheart?

25
00:01:34,845 --> 00:01:39,224
The Doctor, I think. I was...
I don't know. What happened?

26
00:01:39,391 --> 00:01:41,143
You got chosen.

27
00:01:42,311 --> 00:01:44,021
Chosen for what?

28
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:47,232
You're a housemate!
You're in the house. Isn't that brilliant?

29
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:51,153
That's not fair,
we've got eviction in five minutes!

30
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:53,655
I've been here for all nine weeks,
I've followed the rules,

31
00:01:53,739 --> 00:01:56,700
I haven't had a single warning,
then he comes swanning in.

32
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:59,870
If they keep changing the rules,
I'm gonna protest, I am. You watch me.

33
00:01:59,995 --> 00:02:01,705
I'm gonna paint the walls.

34
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,915
(BIG BROTHER THEME MUSIC)

35
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:07,919
Would the Doctor
please come to the Diary Room?

36
00:02:20,724 --> 00:02:25,854
You are live on Channel 44,000.
Please do not swear.

37
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:27,397
You have got to be kidding.

38
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:31,777
(DOCTOR WHO THEME MUSIC)

39
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:15,946
What happened?

40
00:03:16,071 --> 00:03:20,117
It's all right, it's the transmat.
It does your head in.

41
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:23,286
You get a bit of amnesia.
What's your name?

42
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:27,457
Rose. But where's the Doctor?

43
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:32,462
Just remember, do what the android says.
Don't provoke it.

44
00:03:33,088 --> 00:03:35,132
The android's word is law.

45
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:38,135
What do you mean, android?
Like a robot?

46
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:40,846
WOMAN: Positions, everyone.
Thank you!

47
00:03:40,971 --> 00:03:42,806
Come on, hurry up.

48
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:46,852
Steady.

49
00:03:48,812 --> 00:03:52,983
I was traveling...with the Doctor
and a man called Captain Jack.

50
00:03:54,276 --> 00:03:55,902
The Doctor wouldn't just leave me...

51
00:03:55,986 --> 00:04:00,657
That's enough chat.
Positions, final call. Good luck.

52
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:02,617
But I'm not supposed to be here.

53
00:04:02,701 --> 00:04:06,455
It says Rose on the podium.
Come on.

54
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:24,389
Hold on, I must be going mad.

55
00:04:27,017 --> 00:04:29,144
It can't be.
This looks like...

56
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:31,021
Android activated!

57
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:34,065
Oh, my God, the android.

58
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:38,695
The Anne...droid.

59
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:42,032
Welcome to The Weakest Link.

60
00:04:45,327 --> 00:04:48,121
TRINE-E: Here we go again.
We've got our work cut out for us.

61
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:52,209
ZU-ZANA: I don't know, he's sort
of handsome. Has a good lantern jaw.

62
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,711
Lantern jaws are so last year.

63
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:58,215
Sorry, but, nice to meet you, ladies,
but where exactly am I?

64
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,801
We're giving you
a brand-new image.

65
00:05:00,884 --> 00:05:02,719
Hold on,
I was with the Doctor.

66
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:05,305
Why, is there something wrong
with what I'm wearing?

67
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:09,726
It's all very 20th century.
Where did you get that denim?

68
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:13,730
A little place in Cardiff.
It was called The Top Shop.

69
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:16,566
Design classic!

70
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:19,069
But we're going to have to find you
some new colours,

71
00:05:19,194 --> 00:05:23,240
maybe get rid of that "Oklahoma farm boy”
thing you've got going on.

72
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:27,452
Just stand still and let the defabricator
work its magic.

73
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:28,912
What's the defabricator?

74
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,715
Okay. Defabricator.
Does exactly what it says on the tin.

75
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,759
Am I naked in front
of millions of viewers?

76
00:05:42,884 --> 00:05:44,427
BOTH: Absolutely!

77
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:48,557
Ladies...your viewing
figures just went up.

78
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:52,310
Can't open it.

79
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:54,646
It's got a deadlock seal.
Ever since Big Brother 504

80
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:57,440
when they all walked out,
you must remember that?

81
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:58,900
What about this?

82
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:01,570
That's Exoglass.
You need a nuclear bomb to get through.

83
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:03,446
Don't tempt me.

84
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:08,326
I know you're not supposed to talk about
the outside world,

85
00:06:08,451 --> 00:06:11,454
but you must've been watching.
Do people like me?

86
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:13,665
Lynda, Lynda with a "Y"
not Linda with an "I".

87
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:17,794
She got forcibly evicted
'cause she damaged a camera. Am I popular?

88
00:06:18,837 --> 00:06:21,673
-I don't remember.
-Does that mean I'm nothing?

89
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:25,802
Some people get this far 'cause they're
insignificant. Doesn't anybody notice me?

90
00:06:25,969 --> 00:06:30,348
No, you're...nice, you're sweet.
Everybody thinks you're sweet.

91
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:36,187
Oh? Is that right? Is that what I am?
No one's ever told me that before.

92
00:06:36,313 --> 00:06:38,607
Am I sweet? Really?

93
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:40,567
Yeah. Dead sweet.

94
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:42,277
Thank you.

95
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:48,116
It's a wall. Isn't there supposed to be
a garden out there?

96
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,868
Don't be daft,
no one's got a garden anymore.

97
00:06:49,993 --> 00:06:53,038
Who's got a garden?
Don't tell me you've got a garden!

98
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:55,165
No, I've just got the Tardis.

99
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:57,834
I remember.

100
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,503
That's the amnesia! So, what happened?
Where did they get you?

101
00:07:00,712 --> 00:07:02,839
We'd just left
Rexicoricophalvitorius.

102
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:07,218
Then we went to Kyoto.
That's right, Japan, in 1336

103
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:08,845
and we only just escaped.

104
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:11,056
We were together,
we were laughing and then...

105
00:07:11,181 --> 00:07:14,684
there was this light, this white light
coming through the walls

106
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:16,519
and then...

107
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:18,521
I woke up here.

108
00:07:18,647 --> 00:07:21,691
Yeah, that's the transmat beam.
That's how they pick the housemates.

109
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:29,074
Oh, Lynda with a "Y".
Sweet, little Lynda.

110
00:07:30,408 --> 00:07:32,327
It's worse than that.

111
00:07:33,745 --> 00:07:35,830
I'm not just some passing traveller.

112
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:38,875
No stupid little transmat gets inside my ship.

113
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,586
That beam was 15 million
times more powerful.

114
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:45,006
Which means...this isn't just a game.

115
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:47,842
There's something else going on.

116
00:07:50,679 --> 00:07:53,723
Well, here's the latest update
from the Big Brother house.

117
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:57,227
I'm getting out.
I'm gonna find my friends.

118
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:00,730
And then I'm gonna find you.

119
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:13,034
-Need a word.
-Hold on, let me finish this.

120
00:08:13,368 --> 00:08:15,787
19, 18...

121
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:19,749
17,16, 15...

122
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:23,336
Thank you, people, transmitting in...

123
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:26,715
12,11, 10...

124
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,383
I need to find the Doctor...

125
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:30,802
Just shut up and play the game.

126
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:34,973
All right, then.
What the hell, I'm gonna play to win.

127
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:37,934
...and cue!

128
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:42,147
Let's play The Weakest Link.
Start the clock.

129
00:08:42,772 --> 00:08:45,358
Agorax, the name of
which basic foodstuff

130
00:08:45,442 --> 00:08:48,778
ls an anagram of
the word "beard"?

131
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:50,488
-Bread.
-Correct.

132
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:55,243
Fitch, in the Pan Traffic Calendar,
which month comes after Hoob?

133
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:59,414
-Is it Clavadoe?
-No, Pandoft.

134
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:03,668
Rose, in maths,
what is 258 minus 1587

135
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,503
-100!
-Correct.

136
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:06,755
-Rodrick.
-Bank.

137
00:09:06,838 --> 00:09:08,673
Which letter of the alphabet

138
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:12,302
appears in the word dangle
but not in the word gland?

139
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:14,637
-E.
-Correct.

140
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:18,641
Colleen, in social security,
what D is the name of the payment

141
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:20,935
given to Martian Drones?

142
00:09:21,144 --> 00:09:22,729
-Default.
-Correct.

143
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:25,315
Broff, the Great Cobalt Pyramid

144
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:30,445
ls built on the remains
of which famous Old Earth institute?

145
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:33,656
-Touchdown.
-No, Torchwood.

146
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:38,995
Agorax, in language,
all five examples of which type of letter

147
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,581
appear in the word facetious?

148
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:43,083
-Vowels.
-Correct.

149
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:47,962
Fitch, in biology,
which blood cells contain iron, red or white?

150
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:52,092
-White.
-No, red.

151
00:09:52,175 --> 00:09:56,346
Rose, in the holovid series,
Jupiter Rising,

152
00:09:56,471 --> 00:09:58,890
the Grexnik is married to whom?

153
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:01,559
How should I know?

154
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:04,145
Why is she laughing?

155
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:09,901
Oh, my God, I think she knows.

156
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:14,864
And I've got a housemate who appeared
out of nowhere. I told you.

157
00:10:15,198 --> 00:10:16,866
It's like the game's running itself.

158
00:10:17,534 --> 00:10:19,619
It's the Buccaneer look.

159
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:22,539
Little dash of pirate and just a tweak of
President Schwarzenegger.

160
00:10:23,248 --> 00:10:26,209
Not sure about the vest.
What about a little bit of colour to lift it?

161
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:29,170
Absolutely not,
never wear black with colour.

162
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:31,381
It makes the colour look cheap
and the black look boring.

163
00:10:31,506 --> 00:10:33,174
Now, let's talk jackets.

164
00:10:33,258 --> 00:10:36,678
-I kind of like the first one.
-No, that's a bit too much Hell's Angel.

165
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,429
I think I like
the shorter one. Look!

166
00:10:38,555 --> 00:10:41,599
Waist-length, nice and slimming,
shows off the bum.

167
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:42,934
Works for me.

168
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:46,229
Once we've got an outfit,
we can look at the face.

169
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:48,231
Ever thought about
cosmetic surgery?

170
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,608
I've considered it, yeah.
A little lift around the eyes,

171
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,902
tighten up the jaw line,
what do you think?

172
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:55,738
Let's have a bit more ambition.

173
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:59,075
Let's do something cutting edge.

174
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:02,453
So, Rose,
what do you actually do?

175
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:07,375
I just travel about a bit.
Bit of a tourist, I suppose.

176
00:11:08,084 --> 00:11:09,669
Another way of saying unemployed?

177
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,921
. -No!
-Ha ve you got a job?

178
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:14,257
Well, not really, no...

179
00:11:14,424 --> 00:11:15,967
Then you are unemployed.

180
00:11:16,092 --> 00:11:19,596
Yet you've still got enough money
to buy peroxide. Why Fitch?

181
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:24,100
Er...I think she got
a few of the questions wrong, that's all.

182
00:11:25,476 --> 00:11:27,937
And you'd know all about that.

183
00:11:28,271 --> 00:11:32,901
Well, yeah, but I can't vote for myself,
so it had to be Fitch.

184
00:11:35,153 --> 00:11:40,074
Sorry, that's the game, that's how it works.
I had to vote for someone.

185
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:43,745
Let me try again. It was the lights
and everything, I couldn't think...

186
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:48,249
In fact, with three answers wrong,
Broff was the Weakest Link in that round.

187
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:50,001
But it's votes that count!

188
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:54,964
I'm sorry, please.
Oh, God, help me.

189
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:02,847
Fitch, you are
the Weakest Link. Goodbye.

190
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:14,150
And we've gone to the adverts.
Back in three minutes.

191
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:17,528
What's that?
What just happened?

192
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:20,281
She was the Weakest Link,
she gets disintegrated.

193
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:25,328
Blasted into atoms.

194
00:12:25,954 --> 00:12:27,830
But I voted for her.

195
00:12:29,999 --> 00:12:32,210
Oh, my God, this is sick.

196
00:12:33,336 --> 00:12:36,005
All of you, you're just sick.
I'm not playing...

197
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:41,344
I'm not playing!
I can't do it.

198
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:45,723
Please,
somebody let me out of here.

199
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:48,351
You are the Weakest Link.

200
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:52,814
Goodbye.

201
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:01,197
Don't try to escape.

202
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:04,033
It's play or die.

203
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:13,001
Doctor, they said all housemates
must gather on the sofa, you've got to.

204
00:13:13,084 --> 00:13:14,711
I'm busy getting out, thanks.

205
00:13:15,003 --> 00:13:17,922
But if you don't obey,
then all the housemates get punished.

206
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:20,842
Well, maybe I'll be voted out, then.

207
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:24,178
How stupid are you?
You've only just joined, you're not eligible.

208
00:13:24,262 --> 00:13:27,098
And don't try anything clever
or we all get it in the neck.

209
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:30,018
Big Brother house,
this is Davinadroid.

210
00:13:30,101 --> 00:13:32,520
Crosbie, Lynda and Strood,

211
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:36,733
you have all been nominated for eviction.
And the eighth person to be evicted

212
00:13:36,858 --> 00:13:39,193
from the Big Brother house is...

213
00:13:42,071 --> 00:13:44,949
-Crosbie!
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

214
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:48,369
It should've been me,
that's not fair, Crosbie.

215
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:51,414
Crosbie, you have 10 seconds
to make your farewells

216
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:53,416
and then we're going to get you!

217
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:56,002
LYNDA: I won't forget you.

218
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:59,213
-I'm sorry I stole your soap.
-I don't mind, honestly.

219
00:13:59,297 --> 00:14:02,550
And thanks for the food,
you're a smashing cook. Bless you.

220
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:06,637
Crosbie, please leave
the Big Brother house.

221
00:14:11,601 --> 00:14:14,437
Bye, then. Bye, Lynda.

222
00:14:14,729 --> 00:14:16,105
Bye.

223
00:14:27,617 --> 00:14:29,952
I don't believe it. Crosbie.

224
00:14:30,787 --> 00:14:33,456
It's only a game show.
She'll make a fortune on the outside.

225
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:38,127
Sell her story, release a record,
fitness video, all of that. She'll be laughing.

226
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:41,297
-What do you mean, on the outside?
-Here we go.

227
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:44,342
(BIG BROTHER THEME MUSIC)

228
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:53,351
What are they waiting for?
Why don't they just let her go?

229
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:55,478
Stop it, it's not funny.

230
00:14:58,272 --> 00:15:01,567
Eviction in 5, 4...

231
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:05,154
321.

232
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:15,665
What was that?

233
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,335
Disintegrator beam.

234
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:26,467
She's been evicted.

235
00:15:27,844 --> 00:15:29,512
From life.

236
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:39,647
No one programmed the transmat,
no one selected new contestants.

237
00:15:39,856 --> 00:15:41,441
It is exactly like those stories.

238
00:15:41,524 --> 00:15:44,527
Don't start that again.
I think you need to take a session off.

239
00:15:44,694 --> 00:15:46,612
I would,
if you'd take it with me.

240
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:49,240
And don't start that again either.

241
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:50,867
But the rumours go back decades.

242
00:15:50,992 --> 00:15:53,411
Saying that something's been
hidden up here.

243
00:15:53,536 --> 00:15:55,371
Underneath the transmissions.

244
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:59,876
But the Controller would know.
She watches everything.

245
00:16:01,002 --> 00:16:04,714
Maybe she just can't see it.
You've got to allow for human error.

246
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:07,091
Well, that's your problem, then.

247
00:16:08,843 --> 00:16:11,387
I don't think she's been human for years.

248
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:25,109
18, 19, 20.

249
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:27,695
Transmit.

250
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:31,240
Are you insane?
You just step right into the disintegrator?

251
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:34,869
Is it that important getting your face
on the telly? Is it worth dying for?

252
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:38,164
-You're talking like we've got a choice!
-I thought you had to apply.

253
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:41,083
Don't be so stupid.
That's how they played it centuries back.

254
00:16:41,209 --> 00:16:43,503
You get chosen
whether you like it or not.

255
00:16:43,586 --> 00:16:45,630
Everyone on Earth
is a potential contestant,

256
00:16:45,755 --> 00:16:48,007
the transmat beam picks you
out at random.

257
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:51,511
And it's nonstop. There are
60 Big Brother houses all running at once.

258
00:16:51,594 --> 00:16:54,889
-How many? 607?
-They've had to cut back, it's not what it was.

259
00:16:54,972 --> 00:16:57,808
It's a charnel house.
What about the winners? What do they get?

260
00:16:57,934 --> 00:16:59,644
-They get to live.
-Is that it?

261
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:01,938
Well, isn't that enough?

262
00:17:02,939 --> 00:17:06,901
Rose is out there. She got
caught in the transmat, she's a contestant.

263
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:09,362
Time I got out.

264
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:13,032
That other contestant, Linda with an "I",
she was forcibly evicted for what?

265
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:15,952
-Damage to property.
-What, like this?

266
00:17:18,663 --> 00:17:20,957
No, I'm just not getting this.

267
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:25,795
It's just too safe. Too decent.
And you'd never keep it clean.

268
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,547
Stage two ready and waiting.

269
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:29,340
Bring it on, girls.

270
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:37,765
And now it's time
for the face-off!

271
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:40,142
What does that mean?
Do I get to compete with someone else?

272
00:17:40,268 --> 00:17:43,145
No, like I said, face...off.

273
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:45,815
(WHIRRING)

274
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,985
I think you'd look
good with a dog's head!

275
00:17:50,361 --> 00:17:53,406
Or maybe no head at all,
that would be so outrageous.

276
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:56,200
And we could stitch your legs
to the middle of your chest.

277
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:59,328
Nothing is too extreme.
It's to die for.

278
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:02,290
Hold on, ladies, I don't want to have
to shoot either one of you.

279
00:18:02,373 --> 00:18:04,875
-But you're unarmed.
-You're naked!

280
00:18:05,543 --> 00:18:10,214
-But that's a Compact Laser Deluxe.
-Where were you hiding that?

281
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:12,216
You really don't want to know.

282
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:14,135
Give me that accessory!

283
00:18:17,847 --> 00:18:20,808
You are the Weakest Link.
Goodbye.

284
00:18:27,398 --> 00:18:29,734
Going to the break,
two minutes on the clock.

285
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:32,778
Just a reminder, we've got solar flare activity
coming up in 10.

286
00:18:32,862 --> 00:18:34,071
Thanks, everyone.

287
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:37,450
Colleen was clever, she banked all our money,
why'd you vote for her?

288
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:40,119
'Cause I want to keep you in.
You're stupid.

289
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:43,080
You don't even know
the Princess Vossaheen's surname.

290
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:46,417
When it comes to the final,
I want to be up against you.

291
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:50,630
So that you get disintegrated
and I get a stack load of credits.

292
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:53,007
Courtesy of the Bad Wolf Corporation.

293
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,509
What do you mean?
Who's Bad Wolf?

294
00:18:57,553 --> 00:18:59,805
They're in charge,
they run the Game Station.

295
00:18:59,889 --> 00:19:01,515
Why are they called Bad Wolf?

296
00:19:01,599 --> 00:19:03,351
I don't know, it's just a name.

297
00:19:03,434 --> 00:19:05,895
It's like an Old Earth
nursery rhyme sort of thing.

298
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:07,355
What does it matter?

299
00:19:07,438 --> 00:19:11,233
I keep hearing those words
everywhere we go. Bad Wolf.

300
00:19:12,068 --> 00:19:14,195
The things you see...

301
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:16,739
the darkness.

302
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:19,575
The big, bad wolf.

303
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:23,162
Attention all personnel,
Bad Wolf 1 descending.

304
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:24,497
"Blaidd Drwg."

305
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,916
-What's it mean?
-Bad Wolf.

306
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:34,006
Different times, different places.
Like it's written all over the universe.

307
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:35,549
What are you going on about?

308
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:40,054
If the Bad Wolf is in charge of the quiz
then maybe I'm not here by mistake.

309
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:44,725
Someone's been planning this.

310
00:19:45,935 --> 00:19:48,020
The Doctor, you've
broken the house rules.

311
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:50,940
Big Brother has no
choice but to evict you.

312
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:55,403
You have 10 seconds to make your farewells
and then we're gonna get you!

313
00:19:55,486 --> 00:19:58,030
That's more like it!
Come on, then, open up!

314
00:19:58,114 --> 00:19:59,990
You're mad,
it's like you want to die.

315
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:03,369
I reckon he's a plant,
he was only brought in to stir things up.

316
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:06,956
The Doctor,
please leave the Big Brother house.

317
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:12,503
Come on, then, disintegrate me!
Come on, what are you waiting for?

318
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:15,172
He is, he's mad. He's bonkers!

319
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:17,550
I told you to keep
an eye on him, not kill him.

320
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:19,802
He damaged the property,
it's an automatic process.

321
00:20:22,972 --> 00:20:29,186
Evictionin 5, 4, 3, 2, 1.

322
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:33,649
(MACHINES POWER DOWN)

323
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:36,986
Ha-ha! I knew it! You see,
someone brought me into this game.

324
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:39,905
If they wanted me dead,
they could've transmatted me into a volcano.

325
00:20:39,989 --> 00:20:42,032
-What did you do?
-Nothing.

326
00:20:42,158 --> 00:20:44,160
It's like some sort of override.

327
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:47,037
...maybe the security
isn't as tight this end.

328
00:20:47,163 --> 00:20:49,540
You following this?
I'm getting out!

329
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:57,381
-Come with me.
-We're not allowed.

330
00:20:57,506 --> 00:21:00,050
Stay in there,
you got a 50-50 chance of disintegration.

331
00:21:00,176 --> 00:21:03,095
Stay with me, I promise I'll get you out alive.
Come on!

332
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:04,638
No, I can't.

333
00:21:04,722 --> 00:21:07,183
Lynda, you're sweet.
From what I've seen of your world,

334
00:21:07,308 --> 00:21:09,810
do you think
anybody votes for sweet?

335
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:23,866
Hold on.
I've been here before.

336
00:21:24,742 --> 00:21:26,702
This is Satellite Five.

337
00:21:33,584 --> 00:21:35,836
No guards, makes a change.

338
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:39,048
You'd think a big business like Satellite Five
would be armed to the teeth.

339
00:21:39,173 --> 00:21:40,966
No one's called it
Satellite Five in ages.

340
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:44,762
It's the Game Station now.
Hasn't been Satellite Five in about 100 years.

341
00:21:45,179 --> 00:21:49,183
100 years exactly.
It's the year 200100.

342
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:52,019
I was here before, Floor 139.

343
00:21:52,102 --> 00:21:55,189
The Satellite was broadcasting
news channels back then.

344
00:21:55,898 --> 00:21:58,192
Had a bit of trouble upstairs.
Nothing too serious.

345
00:21:58,275 --> 00:22:01,570
Easy, gave them a hand,
home in time for tea.

346
00:22:02,071 --> 00:22:06,909
Hundred years ago? What?
You were here 100 years ago?

347
00:22:07,034 --> 00:22:08,244
Yes.

348
00:22:08,577 --> 00:22:10,246
Well, you're looking good on it.

349
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:12,248
I moisturise.

350
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:16,752
Funny sorts of readings.
All kinds of energy. Place is humming.

351
00:22:16,877 --> 00:22:20,089
It's weird, this goes way beyond
normal transmissions.

352
00:22:20,214 --> 00:22:22,132
What would they need
all that power for?

353
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:26,720
I don't know. I think we're
the first ever contestants to get outside.

354
00:22:27,471 --> 00:22:29,139
I had two friends with me,

355
00:22:29,265 --> 00:22:31,767
they must have got caught in the transmat.
Where would they be?

356
00:22:31,892 --> 00:22:33,894
I don't know,
they could have been allocated anywhere.

357
00:22:33,978 --> 00:22:35,646
There's 100 different games.

358
00:22:35,938 --> 00:22:37,481
Like what?

359
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:39,859
There's 10 floors of Big Brother,
there's a different house

360
00:22:39,942 --> 00:22:43,404
behind each of these doors, and then
beyond that there's all sorts of shows.

361
00:22:43,487 --> 00:22:47,157
It's nonstop.
There's Call My Bluff, with real guns.

362
00:22:47,283 --> 00:22:51,203
Countdown, where you got 30 seconds
to stop the bomb going off.

363
00:22:51,287 --> 00:22:55,916
Ground Force, which is a nasty one.
You get turned into compost.

364
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:57,793
Wipeout, speaks for itself.

365
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:01,839
Oh, and Stars In Their Eyes, literally,
stars in their eyes.

366
00:23:01,964 --> 00:23:04,592
If you don't sing,
you get blinded.

367
00:23:04,675 --> 00:23:06,385
And you watch this stuff?

368
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:08,596
Everyone does.
How come you don't?

369
00:23:08,679 --> 00:23:10,097
Never paid for my license.

370
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:13,100
Oh, my God,
you get executed for that.

371
00:23:13,183 --> 00:23:14,685
Let them try.

372
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:17,897
You keep saying things
that don't make sense.

373
00:23:17,980 --> 00:23:20,024
Who are you,
though, Doctor, really?

374
00:23:21,025 --> 00:23:22,818
It doesn't matter.

375
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:26,363
Well, it does to me.
I've just put my life in your hands.

376
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:31,201
I'm just a traveller wandering past.
Believe it or not, all I'm after is a quiet life.

377
00:23:31,327 --> 00:23:36,206
So, if we get out of here, what are you
going to do? Just wander off again?

378
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:38,125
As fast as I can.

379
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:41,837
'Cause, erm...I could come with you.

380
00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:48,135
-Maybe you could.
-I wouldn't get in the way.

381
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:52,056
I wouldn't mind if you did.
Not a bad idea, Lynda with a "Y".

382
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:57,394
But first of all, we've got to concentrate
on the getting out.

383
00:23:57,519 --> 00:24:00,981
To do that, you've got to know your enemy.
Who's controlling it?

384
00:24:01,065 --> 00:24:03,442
Who's in charge of
the Satellite now?

385
00:24:03,525 --> 00:24:04,818
Hold on.

386
00:24:09,239 --> 00:24:11,909
Your lords and masters.

387
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:22,586
Okay, you win,
the Controller's got to handle this.

388
00:24:22,711 --> 00:24:25,547
Archive makes a record
of all transmat activities.

389
00:24:25,673 --> 00:24:27,341
Find out how he got on board.

390
00:24:27,424 --> 00:24:29,218
Archive 6.

391
00:24:53,742 --> 00:24:56,912
Controller, we have a problem.

392
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:59,289
Continue working.

393
00:24:59,581 --> 00:25:01,250
We have a security problem.

394
00:25:01,375 --> 00:25:03,085
Continue working.

395
00:25:05,295 --> 00:25:09,216
I'm sorry, but I can't.
We have contestants outside of the games.

396
00:25:09,299 --> 00:25:10,968
But the alarms haven't gone off.

397
00:25:11,093 --> 00:25:13,429
No security,
the games continue.

398
00:25:13,971 --> 00:25:15,806
But we can't just let them wander.

399
00:25:15,931 --> 00:25:17,599
They are no one.

400
00:25:20,227 --> 00:25:21,603
They are no one.

401
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,861
I'm sorry, I was just...

402
00:25:28,944 --> 00:25:30,863
Archive 6 is out of bounds.

403
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:32,531
I need to check the transmat log.

404
00:25:32,614 --> 00:25:37,578
Archive 6 is out of bounds.
No one may enter Archive 6. Return to work.

405
00:25:43,959 --> 00:25:45,753
Return to work.

406
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:51,759
Inform all staff,
solar flares in Delta .7.

407
00:25:51,842 --> 00:25:53,761
(MURMURING)

408
00:25:57,431 --> 00:26:01,477
Compatible systems,
just align the wave signature.

409
00:26:02,436 --> 00:26:03,979
Attaboy!

410
00:26:04,104 --> 00:26:08,358
Got myself a gun.
Well, ladies, the pleasure was all mine,

411
00:26:08,484 --> 00:26:10,986
which is the only thing
that matters in the end.

412
00:26:19,620 --> 00:26:22,206
Two hearts, that's him.
Which floor?

413
00:26:28,670 --> 00:26:33,884
Blimey! I've never seen it for real before,
not from orbit.

414
00:26:34,551 --> 00:26:36,136
Planet Earth!

415
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:37,805
What's happened to it?

416
00:26:37,888 --> 00:26:40,891
It's always been like that,
ever since I was born. See that there?

417
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:43,685
That's the Great Atlantic Smog Storm,
it's been going 20 years.

418
00:26:43,811 --> 00:26:46,563
We get newsflashes telling us when
it's safe to breathe outside.

419
00:26:46,688 --> 00:26:49,942
So the population just sits there?
Half the world's too fat

420
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:52,486
and half the world's too thin
and you lot just watch telly?

421
00:26:52,569 --> 00:26:55,030
10,000 channels.
All beaming down from here.

422
00:26:55,155 --> 00:26:58,992
The human race.
Brainless sheep, being fed on a diet of...

423
00:26:59,076 --> 00:27:02,663
Have they still got that program
where three people have to live with a bear?

424
00:27:02,746 --> 00:27:04,331
Bear With Me! I love that!

425
00:27:04,414 --> 00:27:06,750
The celebrity edition
where the bear got in the bath.

426
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:10,337
But it's all gone wrong.
I mean, history's gone wrong. Again!

427
00:27:10,504 --> 00:27:13,215
This should be the Fourth Great
and Bountiful Human Empire.

428
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:16,343
I don't understand.
Last time I was here I put it right.

429
00:27:16,718 --> 00:27:19,179
No, but that's when it first went wrong.
100 years ago.

430
00:27:19,263 --> 00:27:23,600
Like you said, all the news channels,
they just shut down overnight.

431
00:27:24,768 --> 00:27:27,312
But that was me. I did that.

432
00:27:27,396 --> 00:27:29,773
There was nothing left in their place.
No information.

433
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:33,735
The whole planet just froze. The government,
the economy, they collapsed.

434
00:27:33,944 --> 00:27:38,031
That was the start of it.
100 years of hell.

435
00:27:38,115 --> 00:27:39,449
Oh, my...

436
00:27:43,912 --> 00:27:45,706
I made this world.

437
00:27:53,255 --> 00:27:57,718
That leaves Rose and Rodrick.
You're going head-to-head.

438
00:27:58,427 --> 00:28:00,804
Let's play The Weakest Link!

439
00:28:01,430 --> 00:28:05,142
Right, that's the end of tactical voting.
You're on your own now.

440
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:11,148
JACK: Hey, handsome, good to see you.
Any sign of Rose?

441
00:28:11,273 --> 00:28:12,566
Can't you track her down?

442
00:28:12,649 --> 00:28:15,611
She must still be inside the games.
All the rooms are shielded.

443
00:28:15,736 --> 00:28:18,780
If I can just get inside this computer.
She's got to be here somewhere.

444
00:28:18,906 --> 00:28:21,283
You'd better hurry up,
these games don't have a happy ending.

445
00:28:21,408 --> 00:28:23,994
You think I don't know that?

446
00:28:24,411 --> 00:28:27,873
There you go, patch that in.
It's programmed to find her.

447
00:28:27,956 --> 00:28:29,583
-Thanks.
-Hey, there.

448
00:28:29,666 --> 00:28:31,460
-Hello.
-Captain Jack Harkness.

449
00:28:31,627 --> 00:28:33,712
-Lynda Moss.
-Nice to meet you, Lynda Moss.

450
00:28:33,795 --> 00:28:35,964
-Do you mind flirting outside?
-I was just saying hello.

451
00:28:36,089 --> 00:28:37,299
For you, that's flirting.

452
00:28:37,424 --> 00:28:39,509
-I'm not complaining.
-Muchas gracias.

453
00:28:39,635 --> 00:28:42,804
It's not compatible.
This stupid system doesn't make sense.

454
00:28:45,974 --> 00:28:50,520
This place should be a basic broadcaster.
But the systems are twice as complicated.

455
00:28:50,646 --> 00:28:53,774
It's more than just television.
This station's transmitting something else.

456
00:28:53,857 --> 00:28:55,484
-Like what?
-I don't know.

457
00:28:55,609 --> 00:28:57,861
This whole Bad Wolf
thing's tied up with me.

458
00:28:57,986 --> 00:29:00,155
Someone's manipulated my entire life.

459
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,449
It's some sort of trap
and Rose is stuck inside it.

460
00:29:02,532 --> 00:29:03,909
Rose, in geography,

461
00:29:03,992 --> 00:29:07,955
the Grand Central Ravine
ls named after which ancient British city?

462
00:29:08,830 --> 00:29:10,332
Is it York?

463
00:29:10,457 --> 00:29:12,709
No, the correct answer is Sheffield.

464
00:29:12,834 --> 00:29:15,254
Found her. Floor 407.

465
00:29:15,337 --> 00:29:18,090
Oh, my God, she's with the Anne Droid!
You've got to get her out of there!

466
00:29:18,173 --> 00:29:21,969
Rodrick, in literature,
the author of Lucky was Jackie who?

467
00:29:22,052 --> 00:29:23,553
Stewart.

468
00:29:23,679 --> 00:29:26,473
No, the correct answer is Collins.

469
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:31,979
Rose, the oldest inhabitant
of the Isop Galaxy is the Face of what?

470
00:29:32,354 --> 00:29:33,981
Boe! The Face of Boe!

471
00:29:37,192 --> 00:29:39,569
That is the correct answer.

472
00:29:42,531 --> 00:29:44,241
Come on.

473
00:29:45,242 --> 00:29:49,204
Rodrick, in history who was
the President of the Red Velvets?

474
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:50,872
Hoshbin Frane.

475
00:29:50,998 --> 00:29:52,874
That is the correct answer.

476
00:29:53,375 --> 00:29:58,880
Rose, in food, the dish Gaffabeque
originated on which planet?

477
00:30:02,175 --> 00:30:04,386
Erm...is it...

478
00:30:07,389 --> 00:30:10,892
-Mars?
-No, the correct answer is Lucifer.

479
00:30:17,566 --> 00:30:21,069
Rodrick, which measurement of length
ls said to have been defined

480
00:30:21,194 --> 00:30:25,699
by the Emperor Jate as the distance
from his nose to his fingertip?

481
00:30:27,075 --> 00:30:28,994
Would that be a goffle?

482
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:31,455
No, the correct answer is a paab.

483
00:30:31,788 --> 00:30:35,917
Rose, in fashion,
Stella Pok Baint is famous for what?

484
00:30:40,464 --> 00:30:41,882
Shoes.

485
00:30:41,965 --> 00:30:44,092
No, the correct answer is hats.

486
00:30:45,427 --> 00:30:47,679
Game Room 6, which one is it?

487
00:30:47,763 --> 00:30:48,972
Over here!

488
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:51,183
San...Hazeldine?

489
00:30:51,266 --> 00:30:53,852
No, the correct
answer is San Chen.

490
00:30:53,935 --> 00:30:55,520
Stand back,
let me blast it open.

491
00:30:55,604 --> 00:30:57,064
You can't,
it's a vital combination.

492
00:30:57,147 --> 00:31:02,652
Rose, in history, which Icelandic city
hosted Murder Spree 20?

493
00:31:11,453 --> 00:31:12,788
Reykjavik?

494
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:19,127
No, the correct answer is Pola Ventura.

495
00:31:23,965 --> 00:31:27,594
Oh, my God!
I've done it! You've lost!

496
00:31:29,012 --> 00:31:31,348
Come on, come on!

497
00:31:31,473 --> 00:31:34,851
-Rodrick, you are the Strongest Link.
-I'm not meant to be here.

498
00:31:34,976 --> 00:31:37,062
You will be transported home
with 1,600 credits.

499
00:31:37,145 --> 00:31:39,356
I need to find the Doctor!

500
00:31:39,481 --> 00:31:42,234
-He wouldn't just leave me!
-Thank you so much.

501
00:31:42,317 --> 00:31:44,986
This game is illegal,
I'm telling you to stop!

502
00:31:45,112 --> 00:31:48,281
Rose! Stop this game.
I order you to stop this game!

503
00:31:48,365 --> 00:31:52,494
-You are the Weakest link.
-Look out for the Anne Droid, it's armed!

504
00:32:07,884 --> 00:32:10,053
Back off!

505
00:32:10,220 --> 00:32:14,224
I need security and I
need it here right now!

506
00:32:15,350 --> 00:32:18,311
-It's this lot.
-Don't you touch him! Leave him alone!

507
00:32:18,395 --> 00:32:21,189
Sir, put down the gun
or I'll have to shoot.

508
00:32:21,523 --> 00:32:23,400
You killed her!

509
00:32:23,525 --> 00:32:26,361
Your stupid freaking
game show killed her!

510
00:32:26,486 --> 00:32:30,824
Sir, I'm arresting you under
Private Legislation 16 of the Game Station...

511
00:32:48,383 --> 00:32:50,844
Can you tell us the purpose of
this device, sir?

512
00:32:50,927 --> 00:32:53,180
Can you tell us
how you got on board?

513
00:32:53,263 --> 00:32:55,098
Just leave him alone.

514
00:32:56,057 --> 00:32:57,893
I'm asking him.

515
00:33:01,062 --> 00:33:03,732
Sir?
Can you tell us who you are?

516
00:33:10,739 --> 00:33:13,408
You will be taken from this place
to the Lunar Penal Colony,

517
00:33:13,533 --> 00:33:16,912
there to be held without trial.
You may not appeal against this sentence.

518
00:33:19,748 --> 00:33:21,708
Is that understood?

519
00:33:28,632 --> 00:33:30,133
Let's do it.

520
00:33:42,771 --> 00:33:44,731
Oh, my God, now we're in trouble.

521
00:33:46,399 --> 00:33:47,651
Floor 500.

522
00:33:49,945 --> 00:33:53,949
Clear the floor! He's on his way up here.
With a gun!

523
00:33:59,621 --> 00:34:02,040
This is an emergency,
you've got to close down the lift.

524
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:03,416
All staff are
reminded that solar flares...

525
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:06,253
Never mind the solar flares,
he's gonna kill you!

526
00:34:09,339 --> 00:34:13,468
Okay, move away from the desk.
Nobody try anything clever.

527
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:17,180
Everybody clear,
stand to the side and stay there.

528
00:34:17,305 --> 00:34:19,099
Who's in charge of this place?

529
00:34:19,182 --> 00:34:21,810
-This Satellite is more than a Game Station.
-...79, 80...

530
00:34:21,935 --> 00:34:23,311
Who killed Rose Tyler?

531
00:34:23,436 --> 00:34:26,523
-All staff are reminded that...
-I want an answer.

532
00:34:26,648 --> 00:34:28,567
She can't reply. Don't shoot!

533
00:34:28,650 --> 00:34:31,027
Don't be so thick,
like I was ever gonna shoot.

534
00:34:31,194 --> 00:34:32,904
Captain, we've got more
guards on the way up.

535
00:34:32,988 --> 00:34:34,114
-Secure the exits.
-Yes, sir!

536
00:34:34,197 --> 00:34:35,657
You! What were you saying?

537
00:34:35,865 --> 00:34:38,994
-But I've got your gun.
-Okay, so shoot me. Why can't she answer?

538
00:34:39,119 --> 00:34:41,329
She's... Can I put this down?

539
00:34:41,454 --> 00:34:43,582
-If you want, just hurry up.
-Thanks.

540
00:34:43,665 --> 00:34:47,752
Sorry. The Controller
is linked into the transmissions.

541
00:34:47,836 --> 00:34:49,838
The entire output
goes through her brain.

542
00:34:49,963 --> 00:34:52,882
You're not a member of staff
so she doesn't recognise your existence.

543
00:34:53,008 --> 00:34:54,718
-What's her name?
-I don't know.

544
00:34:54,843 --> 00:34:58,179
She was installed when she was five.
It's the only life she's ever known.

545
00:34:58,346 --> 00:35:00,640
Doors sealed.
We should be safe for about 10 minutes.

546
00:35:00,724 --> 00:35:01,850
Keep an eye on them.

547
00:35:01,975 --> 00:35:04,144
What you were saying
about the Game Station,

548
00:35:04,227 --> 00:35:06,187
I think you're right.
I've kept a log.

549
00:35:06,313 --> 00:35:09,983
Unauthorised transmats, encrypted signals,
it's been going on for years.

550
00:35:10,066 --> 00:35:11,151
Show me.

551
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:14,029
You're not allowed in there.
Archive 6 is out of bounds.

552
00:35:14,154 --> 00:35:16,698
Do I look like an out
of bounds sort of guy?

553
00:35:44,059 --> 00:35:45,685
What the hell?

554
00:35:50,357 --> 00:35:52,567
Solar flare activity in Delta .015.

555
00:35:52,734 --> 00:35:56,071
If you're not holding us hostage
then let us out. The staff are terrified.

556
00:35:56,237 --> 00:35:58,740
That's the same staff who execute hundreds
of contestants every day?

557
00:35:58,865 --> 00:36:00,408
We're just doing our jobs.

558
00:36:00,533 --> 00:36:04,079
And with that sentence you just lost
the right to even talk to me, now back off!

559
00:36:08,583 --> 00:36:11,753
That's just the solar flares.
They interfere with the broadcast signal

560
00:36:11,878 --> 00:36:14,172
so this place
automatically powers down.

561
00:36:14,255 --> 00:36:17,926
Planet Earth gets a few repeats.
It's all quite normal.

562
00:36:18,093 --> 00:36:19,427
Doctor...

563
00:36:19,719 --> 00:36:21,930
-Doctor?
-Whatever it is, you can wait.

564
00:36:22,055 --> 00:36:23,848
I think she wants you.

565
00:36:23,932 --> 00:36:28,311
Doctor. Doctor. Where's the Doctor?

566
00:36:28,603 --> 00:36:29,896
I'm here.

567
00:36:29,979 --> 00:36:33,274
Can't see. Blind, so blind.

568
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:37,237
All my life blind, all I can see is numbers.
But I saw you.

569
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:40,865
-What do you want?
-Solar flares hiding me, they can't hear me.

570
00:36:40,949 --> 00:36:42,575
My Masters listen but they can't hear me now.

571
00:36:42,659 --> 00:36:44,327
The sun is so bright.

572
00:36:44,452 --> 00:36:46,329
Who are your masters?

573
00:36:46,454 --> 00:36:50,417
They wired my head, the name's forbidden.
They control my thoughts.

574
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:53,086
My Masters,
I had to be careful.

575
00:36:53,169 --> 00:36:56,256
They monitor transmission
but they don't watch the programs.

576
00:36:56,339 --> 00:36:58,883
I could hide you in the games.
I knew that you'd find me.

577
00:36:58,967 --> 00:37:00,802
My friend died inside your games.

578
00:37:00,927 --> 00:37:02,887
-Doesn't matter.
-Don't dare tell me that!

579
00:37:02,971 --> 00:37:06,641
They've been hiding.
My Masters, hiding in the dark space.

580
00:37:06,766 --> 00:37:10,854
Watching and shaping the Earth,
SO many years.

581
00:37:11,646 --> 00:37:15,734
Always been there, guiding humanity.
Hundreds and hundreds of years.

582
00:37:15,817 --> 00:37:17,110
Who are they?

583
00:37:17,193 --> 00:37:19,821
They wait and plan and grow in numbers,
they're strong now.

584
00:37:19,946 --> 00:37:22,323
-So strong, my Masters...
-Who are they?

585
00:37:22,449 --> 00:37:25,827
But speak of you, my Masters,
they fear the Doctor...

586
00:37:25,952 --> 00:37:28,496
Tell me, who are they?

587
00:37:31,332 --> 00:37:33,001
(MURMURING)

588
00:37:35,003 --> 00:37:36,421
When's the next solar flare?

589
00:37:36,504 --> 00:37:38,590
-Two years' time.
-Fat lot of good that is!

590
00:37:38,673 --> 00:37:40,884
-Found the Tardis.
-We're not leaving now.

591
00:37:41,009 --> 00:37:45,513
No, but the Tardis worked it out.
You'll wanna watch this.

592
00:37:45,638 --> 00:37:47,807
Lynda, could you
stand over there for me, please?

593
00:37:47,891 --> 00:37:49,517
I just want to go home.

594
00:37:49,642 --> 00:37:53,313
It'll only take a second. Could you stand
in that spot? Quick as you can.

595
00:37:53,396 --> 00:37:57,859
Everybody watching?
Okay, 3, 2, 1.

596
00:38:03,239 --> 00:38:06,034
-But you killed her.
-Oh? Do you think?

597
00:38:10,914 --> 00:38:12,791
What the hell was that?

598
00:38:12,874 --> 00:38:15,543
It's a transmat beam.
Not a disintegrator.

599
00:38:15,668 --> 00:38:19,672
A secondary transmat system.
People don't get killed in the games.

600
00:38:19,756 --> 00:38:24,010
They get transported across space.
Doctor, Rose is still alive!

601
00:38:38,691 --> 00:38:40,777
No. It can't be...

602
00:38:41,945 --> 00:38:44,739
You're dead. I saw you die!

603
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:52,747
-She's out there somewhere.
-Doctor! Coordinates 5.6.1.

604
00:38:52,872 --> 00:38:54,791
Don't! The solar flare's gone,
they'll hear you!

605
00:38:54,916 --> 00:38:58,461
...434. No, my Masters, no, I defy you!

606
00:38:58,586 --> 00:39:01,297
Sigma 77... (SCREAMS)

607
00:39:03,424 --> 00:39:05,260
They took her.

608
00:39:24,946 --> 00:39:26,614
My Masters.

609
00:39:28,283 --> 00:39:32,453
You can kill me.
For I have brought your destruction.

610
00:39:39,002 --> 00:39:41,379
Use that, it might
contain the final numbers.

611
00:39:41,462 --> 00:39:43,965
I kept a log of all
the unscheduled transmissions.

612
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:48,511
Nice, thanks.
Captain Jack Harkness, by the way.

613
00:39:48,636 --> 00:39:51,556
-I'm Davitch Pavale.
-Nice to meet you, Davitch Pavale.

614
00:39:51,639 --> 00:39:53,224
There's a time and a place.

615
00:39:53,308 --> 00:39:56,185
Are you saying this whole setup's been
a disguise all along?

616
00:39:56,436 --> 00:39:59,522
Going way back.
Installing the Jagrafess 100 years ago.

617
00:39:59,647 --> 00:40:01,816
Someone's been
playing a long game.

618
00:40:01,941 --> 00:40:05,403
Controlling the human race
from behind the scenes for generations.

619
00:40:05,486 --> 00:40:07,322
Click on this.

620
00:40:10,992 --> 00:40:14,954
The transmat delivers to that point,
right on the edge of the solar system.

621
00:40:15,038 --> 00:40:16,623
There's nothing there.

622
00:40:16,706 --> 00:40:19,834
It looks like nothing
because that's what this Satellite does!

623
00:40:19,959 --> 00:40:22,503
Underneath the transmission,
there's another signal.

624
00:40:22,629 --> 00:40:25,673
-Doing what?
-Hiding whatever's out there.

625
00:40:25,798 --> 00:40:28,176
Hiding it from sonar,
radar, scanners.

626
00:40:28,968 --> 00:40:31,763
There's something sitting
right on top of planet Earth

627
00:40:31,846 --> 00:40:34,140
but it's completely invisible.

628
00:40:34,223 --> 00:40:36,559
If I cancel the signal...

629
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:57,664
That's impossible.
I know those ships.

630
00:40:58,206 --> 00:40:59,999
They were destroyed.

631
00:41:01,042 --> 00:41:02,794
Obviously they survived.

632
00:41:02,877 --> 00:41:04,712
Who did? Who are they?

633
00:41:04,837 --> 00:41:09,342
200 ships.
More than 2,000 on board each one.

634
00:41:09,425 --> 00:41:11,511
That's just about half a million of them.

635
00:41:11,594 --> 00:41:13,471
Half a million what?

636
00:41:13,554 --> 00:41:15,014
Daleks.

637
00:41:16,015 --> 00:41:19,602
Alert. Alert. We are detected!

638
00:41:19,727 --> 00:41:25,441
It is the Doctor! He has located us.
Open communications channel.

639
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:30,238
The female will stand. Stand!

640
00:41:37,245 --> 00:41:39,706
I will talk to the Doctor.

641
00:41:40,123 --> 00:41:42,250
Oh, will you?
That's nice. Hello.

642
00:41:42,375 --> 00:41:47,463
The Dalek Stratagem nears completion.
The Fleet is almost ready.

643
00:41:47,588 --> 00:41:49,590
You will not intervene.

644
00:41:49,924 --> 00:41:51,509
Oh, really? Why's that, then?

645
00:41:51,592 --> 00:41:53,928
We have your associate.

646
00:41:54,929 --> 00:41:58,891
You will obey or she
will be exterminated.

647
00:42:01,269 --> 00:42:02,729
No.

648
00:42:08,609 --> 00:42:10,778
Explain yourself.

649
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,613
I said, no.

650
00:42:13,072 --> 00:42:15,658
What is
the meaning of this negative?

651
00:42:15,783 --> 00:42:17,285
It means no.

652
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:19,495
But she will be destroyed!

653
00:42:19,662 --> 00:42:24,584
No, 'cause this is what I'm gonna do.
I'm gonna rescue her.

654
00:42:24,667 --> 00:42:27,587
I'm gonna save Rose Tyler
from the middle of the Dalek Fleet.

655
00:42:27,670 --> 00:42:31,007
And then I'm gonna save the Earth.
And then, just to finish off,

656
00:42:31,132 --> 00:42:35,303
I'm gonna wipe every
last stinking Dalek out of the sky!

657
00:42:35,428 --> 00:42:39,932
But you have no weapons!
No defences! No plan!

658
00:42:40,016 --> 00:42:43,644
Yeah. And doesn't
that scare you to death?

659
00:42:44,479 --> 00:42:45,521
Rose?

660
00:42:45,646 --> 00:42:46,939
Yes, Doctor?

661
00:42:47,023 --> 00:42:48,983
I'm coming to get you.

662
00:42:49,776 --> 00:42:52,820
The Doctor is
initiating hostile action.

663
00:42:52,945 --> 00:42:58,367
The Stratagem must advance.
Begin the invasion of Earth.

664
00:42:58,493 --> 00:43:00,995
The Doctor will
be exterminated.

665
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:04,999
ALL: Exterminate.
Exterminate...

666
00:43:13,508 --> 00:43:16,302
Launch missiles. Exterminate.

667
00:43:17,386 --> 00:43:21,724
We've got incoming.
This is it, ladies and gentlemen, we are at war.

668
00:43:22,058 --> 00:43:25,186
JACK: There's an army
about to invade this station.

669
00:43:26,229 --> 00:43:27,522
Defences have gone off line.

670
00:43:27,647 --> 00:43:31,651
I'm dead, or about to die any second,
with no chance of escape.

671
00:43:44,747 --> 00:43:46,791
How did you
survive the Time War?

672
00:43:46,874 --> 00:43:49,877
They survived through me.

